        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=40989&amp;TOPIC_ID=5117&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Guild+Problem%2C+please+help&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         There are many variables. If someone is playing a wizard but has a druid standing by for buffing are they really playing the druid?</P><P>Guilds using point systems usually assign points by player, you can spend your points on any character if you want but having extras present doesn't increase your chances at loot.</P><P>Other options might be<BR>1. Pick a character, thats the one that gets to roll for loot on that raid.<BR>2. A player can roll for anything any of their characters present can use but the minute they get something it's counted against all the characters present. Got a cleric and a warrior and you won the roll for your cleric? Congratulations you have to wait for all the clerics and warriors to recieve loot before you're allowed to roll again</P><P>Whatever you choose just make sure it's clear before the raid begins :) Nothing worse than determining loot policy *after* that sweet rare item drops</P><P></P><P>Narben the Gnome Gnecro<BR>Colleague of Sanctuary<BR>Luclin server<BR>"Find your own damn witty comment"<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

