         The way my guild does it is that you spend points (ELP) from your main and only for your main.  If you want to switch your main, you spend an insane amount of points to do that.  It actually works out pretty good.  People make the choice to two box, but they understand that they can only spend points for their main.</P><P>Xuraz Xorthexia - <BR>Warlock<BR>Xegony Server<BR>Profile - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
