        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         the guild I normally raid with will only give "desired" items to one character that you play. Doesn't matter if you have a 60 warrior and a 60 cleric, only one of them gets labelled as you "main" and them and only them will get considered on loot.</P><P>Course it should be noted that most loot is assigned by the guild master rather than rolled, but the lesson still stands.</P><P>Any other characters you bring on raids are treated as twinks, and generally only get loot if no one else on a "main" wants it.</P><P>Seems reasonably fair to me. Given that boss mobs can be killed only a set number of times per week and only a set number of items drop, there has to be some way to ensure even distribution.</P><P>Pickup raids I'd weigh differently, especially when loot is being /randomed. Each character that is on the raid should be entitled to their own roll. Pickups are by definition very mercenery situations, everyone is cooperating with the knowledge that they wouldn't have any chance at loot if they were alone. Which is why I think those situations permit different rulesets.</P><P><a href="http://tru7h.org/absor/" target="_blank">http://tru7h.org/absor/</a> -  ask absor anything!<BR><a href="http://xzzy.org/ereet/" target="_blank">http://xzzy.org/ereet/</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
