         I've been playing my warrior and my shaman together for about 18 months now.  I DARE anyone to notice that I play them both without looking at the chat.  Obviously, i only type things on one computer, but I am VERY good at playing both characters now...my shaman is not just my 'buff bitch."</P><P>A friend convinced me to give his uberguild a crack.  I got an unsolicited invite from a guild officer for both of my characters before they knew i played them both.  The next day the guild leader told me to pick a main to get loot.  Well i'm sorry, but if that's the way it's gonna be, then i'll be damned if i'm playing both characters to benefit your raids if only one character gets rewarded.  I'm not busting my ass to play 2 characters on a raid and get loot for one, so I left.  Simple as that.</P><P>Sure, i'll agree, the vast majority of people 2 boxing suck at it and shouldn't deserve it...but there are a few of us out there who genuinely can make things go smoother with 2 characters and we shouldn't be lumped in with the morons.</P><P>And of course, the best thing to do is -- if you don't like it, leave.  I put my money where my mouth is.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
