        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         as someone who now has 2 accounts on 2 diferent computers I never made the second account to raid with my guild. If they asked me to bring my shaman along then I believe he should also have a chance at any shaman only or shaman rolled loot that drops. My guild doesn't do anything harder than Hole-Reavers in CoM atm but we will get there someday. As for the loot that we go after, it is usually said at the beginning of the raid who would get what item if it drops. When we do reavers we go for a specific item. The ones that can use the reavers when they drop get a chance to roll until everyone in the guild that needs one gets one. We as a guild decided after everyone that needs one for epic/upgrade gets one, the rest will be randomed to the guild members and guild bank for fundings. Someday we will have to deal with loot on a much larger scale but 99% of the people in our guild are not greedy and always go NBG. The one thing that does annoy me is if no one on the raid needs the item most of the time the guild bank gets it instead of randoming it off to anyone on the raid. Sucks because right now my guild doesn't sell items in the bank they just loan them out for a specific time to alts etc that can use them and then they are required to give the item back to the bank later.</P><P>Vendicater Vin`Dictor<BR>Dark Elf Necromancer <BR>Level 52.5<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
