        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Thinking as RL people and not toons....</P><P>Wouldn't you first be bringing both characters on the raid to help the guild in general and therefore maybe increasing the amount or quality of loot that dropped even if both of them were not able to get loot at that time? </P><P>I know people will say "IF both cant get loot than I'm only bringing one and that's there perogative. But, if we merited loot to one person's two toons then aren't we doubling there chance for loot and possibley hurting someone else who only plays one character?</P><P>I know it seems unfair either way, but it also seems to be more fair to the guild as a WHOLE to have an equal playing field with loot. Where everyone(RL) gets one chance a said loot. If I had two characters, one cleric and one wizard and I had been in the guild for 6 months and the was another cleric and wizard on the raid. Cleric had been in for 3 months and wizard for 1 month. All of us particpated about the same amount and none of us had BP's. the 1 cleric BP and 1 wizzy robed dropped. I would seriously feel bad if I Was meritted both. Wouldn't you?</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
